# Vercel Speed Insights Integration

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js application following the official Vercel documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **File**: `apps/web/package.json`
- **Action**: Installed `@vercel/speed-insights@^2.0.0` as a dependency
- **Command**: `npm install @vercel/speed-insights --workspace=web`

### 2. Component Configuration
- **File**: `apps/web/app/layout.tsx`
- **Action**: Added SpeedInsights component to root layout
- **Changes**:
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the body, after `<AdvisingBot />`
  
### 3. Lock File Update
- **File**: `package-lock.json`
- **Action**: Updated with the new dependency and its transitive dependencies

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide for Next.js 13.5+ projects:
- Retrieved latest documentation from: https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart
- Used the Next.js-specific import path: `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Placed the component at the root layout level to track performance across all pages
- Positioned the component at the end of the body element as recommended by the documentation

## Framework & Package Manager
- **Framework**: Next.js 16.2.9 (latest)
- **Package Manager**: npm 10.9.2 (workspace monorepo)
- **Project Type**: Next.js App Router with TypeScript

## Verification
- ✅ Package successfully installed
- ✅ No TypeScript errors introduced
- ✅ No linting errors in modified layout.tsx file
- ✅ Lock file properly updated
- ✅ Code follows existing project patterns and conventions

## Next Steps
To enable Speed Insights monitoring:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Vercel dashboard
3. Select "Speed Insights" from the sidebar
4. Choose the project and click "Enable"
5. Performance metrics will appear in the dashboard after users visit the site

## Notes
- The SpeedInsights component is added at the root layout level, making it available site-wide
- Pre-existing linting errors in other files remain unchanged (not related to this implementation)
- Build failure due to missing Supabase environment variables is unrelated to Speed Insights changes
- The integration is non-invasive and maintains the existing code structure
